ay"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Present a variety of materials for building a house, including blocks, books, pieces of paper, pipe cleaners, playing cards, and magnetic tiles. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"As a class, discuss the merits of each building material. Have children work in groups to build a house with the material of their choice. After, discuss the strength of each house."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Guided Writing"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Provide a writing prompt about building and give ongoing feedback as children draw and write in response to the prompt."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"child-development-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_hed-green","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Child Development: Vocabulary"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_body","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Expanding children’s vocabulary with academic terms opens up possibilities to children both in school and outside. Encourage children to use academic vocabulary they have learned throughout the day and in different contexts. Remind them that when they hear terms they do not know, they can ask what the words mean, including outside of school."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"day_5","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"week","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header_all-caps","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"LET’S CREATE  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_header_separator","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"|"}]},{"type":"text","text":"  WEEK 4: Build It"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"circle-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_5","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Connect to Physical Science"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Point out the ways Bird pushes and pulls materials in the book. Ask children to provide more examples of pushing and pulling from life."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_5","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Build a Nest Song"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Sing a version of “"},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_emphasis","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Row, Row, Row Your Boat"}]},{"type":"text","text":"” with children using build a nest/build it out of sticks/cozily/ make it nice for chicks. As you sing, act out building a nest like Bird."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_5","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Focus on Vocabulary"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Review two vocabulary words. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use 6.4.3 Vocabulary Cards."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_vocab_words","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"heavy light"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"story-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit the Book "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Show the book cover."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Today we are going to retell "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Bird Builds a Nest "}]},{"type":"text","text":"by Martin Jenkins and illustrated by Richard Jones."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the Lala Stick Puppet."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Lala likes stories that help her learn new information!"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Share the Guiding Question"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"We saw that Bird found and used twigs, feathers, and leaves to build her cozy nest. As we read the story today, think about this guiding question:"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_guiding-question_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Why did Bird build a nest? "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Read-Aloud: Retell and Reenact"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s reread the book one more time together. This time, we will act like Bird and notice what is heavy and light."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 8–9"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Bird eats worms for breakfast. She pulls hard to get worms out of the ground. Let’s pretend to pull worms out of the ground. It’s hard!"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 11"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Bird needs light sticks to build her nest. Why do they need to be light? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 14–15"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s pretend to carry as many twigs as we can. Can you carry three? Can you carry two more? How many would you be carrying in all?"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"page 17"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Bird pushes and pulls all the twigs to turn them into her nest. Are heavy or light things easier to push and pull? Let’s push and pull on imaginary twigs! "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 21–22"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let’s pretend to carry feathers and dried grass. We can carry a lot more because these are light! Why does Bird want soft building materials for her nest? "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 23–25"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Bird has been getting the nest ready. There were no eggs, and now there are five! Let’s pretend to curl up in our cozy nests."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Talk About It"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s talk about the guiding question. Why did Bird build a nest? "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Ask children to "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Turn and Talk."}]},{"type":"text","text":" Use Equity Sticks to choose several children to share their responses."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Possible responses:"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_bulleted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"She built a nest to have a cozy place to live."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_bulleted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"She built a nest to hold her eggs."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_bulleted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"She built a nest for her family."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Independent Writing"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Invite children to draw or write about a house they wish to build and what materials they’d use."}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_hed_support-challenge","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Support"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_numbers","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"1"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Who is Bird building the nest for?"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_numbers","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"2"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Bird is building the nest for her e"},{"type":"element","name":"fill-in-the-blank","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"___"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(eggs)."}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_numbers","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"3"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Bird is building the nest for her eggs."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_hed_support-challenge","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Challenge"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"A nest is a house. Why do we build houses?"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"child-development-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_hed-green","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Child Development: Measurement"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_body","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Preschool children mostly think of weight informally: they estimate which of two objects is harder to push and pull, they ask themselves which feels heavier in their hands, and, often, they guess by just looking at the objects. When discussing the weight of objects, remind children that weight is determined by material and size."}]}]}]}]}]}]}]